      "header": "Overview and Common Uses",
      "content": "Moxidectin is a macrocyclic lactone belonging to the milbemycin chemical class. It is primarily used as an anthelmintic agent to control parasitic infections. Initially developed for veterinary applications, moxidectin is utilized in animals such as dogs, cats, cattle, and horses to treat and prevent infestations by various parasites, including nematodes and ectoparasites. In 2018, the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) approved moxidectin for human use to treat onchocerciasis, commonly known as river blindness, a disease caused by the parasitic worm Onchocerca volvulus.",
