      "header": "Regulatory and Monitoring Context",
      "content": "Moxidectin received FDA approval in 2018 for the treatment of onchocerciasis in adults and adolescents aged 12 years and older. The European Medicines Agency (EMA) has evaluated moxidectin for veterinary use, establishing maximum residue limits in food-producing animals to ensure consumer safety. Monitoring practices include pharmacovigilance programs to track adverse effects and efficacy in both human and veterinary applications."
